subject: Re: [junit] asserEquals question
msgSnippet: ... Recompile everything in your project. Maybe you have a compile problem somewhere in a dependent library. -- J. B. Rainsberger, Diaspar Software Services
messageBody:
junitj wrote:

> I have a problem when I tried to use asserEquals methos inside my
> test case, I got the error :
> "java.lang.NoSuchMethodError:assertEquals
> (Ljava/lang/String;Ljava/lang/String;Ljava/lang/String;)V"
>
> I tried to remove the junit.jar from the IDE (Intellij) and reload
> it, sometimes it works and sometimes the error return back.

Recompile everything in your project. Maybe you have a compile problem
somewhere in a dependent library.
